                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/32.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consular Agent <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guaymas</hi>
                        </placeName> (<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>
                        <hi rend="italic">; received December 12, 1913</hi>).</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Additional exorbitant war tax five per cent on business capital imposed by
                    Provisional Governor here payable by December 17, refusal involving penalties.
                    German merchants have wired the German Ambassador, Washington, D. C, claiming
                    exemption according to treaty between Mexico and Germany. American and Chinese
                    merchants, referring to Article III, commercial treaty between the United States
                    and Mexico of 1831, beg your early advice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
